# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **File Modified**: `package.json`
- **Action**: Added `@vercel/speed-insights` (v2.0.0) as a dependency
- **Command Used**: `npm install @vercel/speed-insights`

### 2. Lock File Updated
- **File Modified**: `package-lock.json`
- **Action**: Updated to include the new dependency and its transitive dependencies (26 packages added)

### 3. SpeedInsights Component Integration
- **File Modified**: `src/app/layout.js`
- **Actions**:
  - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the children
  - This follows the Next.js App Router pattern as specified in the official documentation

## Implementation Details

### Framework Configuration
- **Framework**: Next.js 16.2.2 with App Router
- **Package Manager**: npm
- **Integration Pattern**: Added SpeedInsights to root layout (`src/app/layout.js`) following Next.js v13.5+ guidelines

### Code Changes
The SpeedInsights component was added to the root layout file following the recommended placement pattern:
```javascript
<body>
  {children}
  <SpeedInsights />
</body>
```

This ensures Speed Insights tracking is enabled across all pages of the application while maintaining server-side rendering capabilities.

## Verification

### Build Verification
- Ran `npm run build` successfully
- Next.js compiled without errors
- Build output confirms all routes are properly configured
- No TypeScript/compilation errors

### Code Quality
- Changes maintain existing code structure and formatting
- No breaking changes to existing functionality
- SpeedInsights component is non-intrusive and follows React best practices

## Next Steps

To enable Speed Insights data collection:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel project dashboard
3. Monitor performance metrics through the Vercel dashboard after deployment and user visits

## Notes
- Speed Insights will automatically track Web Vitals (CLS, FID, LCP, FCP, TTFB, INP)
- The integration is lightweight and won't impact page performance
- Data will appear in the Vercel dashboard after deployment and sufficient user traffic
